Course Overview:
The primary focus of this course is to address challenges in ecological remote sensing, with a specific emphasis on planetary changes. It is thoughtfully designed for scholars who have little or no prior experience with R. Throughout the duration of the course, we will start from the very basics in R and guide attendees through the step-by-step process of coding remote sensing analysis.
 
Learning Objectives:
By the end of this course, participants will achieve the following learning outcomes:
Opening and managing a GitHub account to efficiently store and collaborate on code.
Mastering the fundamentals of coding in R, from the basics to remote sensing data analysis.
Receiving a comprehensive introduction to LaTeX for coding texts and effectively reporting findings.
Course Format:
The sessions will be a blend of interactive lectures, hands-on coding exercises, and practical demonstrations. Participants will have the opportunity to engage with experienced instructors who will provide continuous support throughout the learning journey.
 
